fields.option_text: The Retailer (or Producer) can offer to sell (buy back) the excess of units in Stage 2 until the Retailer (or Producer) has exactly the same number as UNITS DEMANDED.
fields.explanation_text: This is correct. A Retailer will not be credited for holding extra units above the UNITS DEMANDED, and can thus earn some extra profit by selling the extra units. A Producer that has sold more units than the number of UNITS DEMANDED increases his profit by buying back units when the price for these units is below the Producer's production costs.

fields.option_text: When a Retailers (or Producer) has more units than the number of UNITS DEMANDED in Stage 2, nothing can be done and the Retailer (or Producer) must just accept that they lose a little bit of profit here.
fields.explanation_text: This is incorrect as both Retailers and Producers are allowed to sell and buy in both Stage 1 and Stage 2.
